{
  "texts": [
    "RISE was primarily designed for use with audio problems, where spectral features are more likely to be discriminatory.",
    "Supervised Time Series Forest (STSF) (Cabello et al. 2020) is an interval based tree ensemble that includes a supervised method for extracting intervals.",
    "Intervals are found and extracted for a periodogram and the first order differences representation as well as the base series.",
    "STSF introduces bagging for each tree and extracts seven simple summary statistics from each interval.",
    "For each tree, an initial split point for the series is randomly selected."
  ]
}